<div class="post-header mb2">
  <h2>PICAutoDroid, Mobile Robot using PIC18F452 8-bit microcontroller</h2>
  <span class="post-meta">December 1, 2012 to March 15, 2013</span><br>
  
  <span class="post-meta small">
  
    4 minutes read
  
  </span>
</div>
<article class="post-content">
  <script type="text/javascript" src="http://cdn.mathjax.org/mathjax/latest/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS-MML_HTMLorMML"></script>
<p>PICAutoDroid was my hobby project. The brain of the robot is the <a href="http://www.microchip.com/wwwproducts/Devices.aspx?product=PIC18F452">PIC18F452 8-bit microcontroller</a> coupled with <a href="http://www.microchip.com/wwwproducts/Devices.aspx?product=RN42">RN-42 Bluetooth module</a>. 
The robot is controlled by an android app. An android device with built-in gyroscope has been used. Gyroscope senses angular velocity of the device and outputs the 
digital data. The commands are derived from the data. The commands are sent to the robot over wireless Bluetooth communication link. Also, the robot is commanded through voice commands. </p>.   
</article>

<figure>
  <img src="/assets/picauto.png" />
  <figcaption>The components and android app</figcaption>
</figure>

<h3 id="formulation-of-the-problem">Design</h3>

<h4 id="input">Input</h4>
<p>The control commands to the robot are the function of gyroscope sensor data. The angular position of the android device is input to the robot. 
The voice commands from the android device are also used to teach the robot.</p>

<h4 id="output">Output</h4>
<p>Microcontroller generates PWM signals to control the speed of the DC motor based on the input commands.</p>

<h3 id="algorithm-outline">Hardware</h3>

<p>Bluetooth module RN-42 communicates with the microcontroller through UART at 19200 baud rate. The RN-42 receives commands from the android device and feeds them to microcontroller.</p>
<p>  <a href="http://probots.co.in/index.php?main_page=product_info&cPath=54&products_id=361#.Vidkta2lyko">L293 based Motor Driver</a> has been used to control the speed and the direction of the DC motors.</p> 

<h3 id="algorithm-outline">Software</h3>
The working code will be uploaded soon on the GitHub.

